Pacquiao, a resounding underdog for the May 2 showdown at Las Vegas’s MGM Grand, has come out fighting long before the bell saying Mayweather’s fights put him to sleep and urging the master tactician to fight aggressively.

The 36-year-old’s confident jibes come even before the pair face-off in Los Angeles for their only joint press conference in the lead-up to the fight. 

‘I'm here to prove that I can easily beat the undefeated,’ Pacquiao said on ESPN in comments shared by his minders on Twitter.

