‘I am very happy that Floyd Mayweather and I can give the fans the fight they have wanted for so many years.’

Pacquiao, boxing’s only eight-division world champion, added his nimble feet and combinations will give him the edge over the American with an imposing 47-0 record, and that his bouts against Miguel Cotto and Oscar De La Hoya instilled more fear in him.

‘My footwork and hand combinations will be my advantage,’ he said. ‘I tell you Cotto and Margarito punch hard. This is boxing and its about punches.’ 

